# Gmail MCP Server - Environment Variables Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ==============================================================================
# GOOGLE OAUTH 2.0 CREDENTIALS
# ==============================================================================
# These credentials are obtained from Google Cloud Console
# Follow setup instructions in QUICKSTART.md or AUTHENTICATION.md

# Your OAuth 2.0 Client ID from Google Cloud Console
# Format: xxxxxxxxxxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
# Where to get: Google Cloud Console > APIs & Services > Credentials
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Your OAuth 2.0 Client Secret from Google Cloud Console
# Format: GOCSPX-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Where to get: Same location as Client ID
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# OAuth 2.0 Redirect URI (for local development)
# Default: http://localhost:3000/oauth2callback
# Must match EXACTLY what's configured in Google Cloud Console
# Change the port if 3000 is already in use on your system
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/oauth2callback

# ==============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Create Google Cloud Project:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Create a new project or select existing one
#
# 2. Enable Gmail API:
#    - Navigate to "APIs & Services" > "Library"
#    - Search for "Gmail API"
#    - Click "Enable"
#
# 3. Create OAuth 2.0 Credentials:
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
#    - Choose "Desktop app" as application type
#    - Name it (e.g., "Gmail MCP Server")
#    - Click "Create"
#
# 4. Copy Credentials:
#    - Download the JSON file OR
#    - Copy the Client ID and Client Secret from the console
#    - Paste them into this file
#
# 5. Configure OAuth Consent Screen (if not done):
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "OAuth consent screen"
#    - Choose "External" for testing
#    - Fill in required fields (App name, User support email, Developer email)
#    - Add yourself as a test user under "Test users"
#    - Save
#
# 6. Required OAuth Scopes:
#    The app requests these scopes automatically:
#    - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify
#      (Read, compose, send, and permanently delete emails)
#    - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.settings.basic
#      (Manage basic mail settings)
#
# ==============================================================================
# ALTERNATIVE: CREDENTIALS FILE
# ==============================================================================
#
# Instead of using environment variables, you can use a credentials.json file.
# Download the JSON file from Google Cloud Console and save it as:
# credentials.json in the project root directory.
#
# The app will automatically detect and use credentials.json if present.
# Environment variables take precedence over credentials.json.
#
# ==============================================================================
# USAGE
# ==============================================================================
#
# Option 1: Use .env file (recommended for development)
# - Copy this file to .env
# - Fill in your actual values
# - The app will automatically load .env variables
#
# Option 2: Export environment variables (recommended for production)
# - Linux/Mac:
#   export GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your-client-id"
#   export GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your-client-secret"
#   export GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI="http://localhost:3000/oauth2callback"
#
# - Windows (PowerShell):
#   $env:GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your-client-id"
#   $env:GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your-client-secret"
#   $env:GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI="http://localhost:3000/oauth2callback"
#
# - Windows (Command Prompt):
#   set GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
#   set GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
#   set GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/oauth2callback
#
# ==============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================================================
#
# - NEVER commit .env file to version control
# - .env is already in .gitignore
# - Keep credentials secure and private
# - Rotate credentials if compromised
# - Use different credentials for development and production
# - Review granted permissions regularly in your Google Account settings
#
# ==============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ==============================================================================
#
# Issue: "Gmail OAuth credentials not configured!"
# Solution: Ensure GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET are set
#
# Issue: "Access blocked: This app's request is invalid"
# Solution: Add yourself as a test user in OAuth consent screen
#
# Issue: Port 3000 already in use
# Solution: Change GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI to use a different port (e.g., 3001)
#          and update the redirect URI in Google Cloud Console to match
#
# Issue: "redirect_uri_mismatch"
# Solution: Ensure GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI exactly matches what's configured
#          in Google Cloud Console (including protocol, port, and path)
#
